<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1300}{e}^{{{0.09}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 2441.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <fillin characters="20"/> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>7.0004836327037</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1300}{e}^{{{0.09}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{2441}={1300}{e}^{{{0.09}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{2441}}{{1300}}={e}^{{{0.09}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{2441}}{{1300}}\right)}}}={0.09}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{2441}}{{1300}}\right)}}}}{{0.09}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={7.0004836327037}</m></p>
</solution>
